    "Then, we carry experiments in two steps: indexing building and query answering, with caches cleared before each step and kept warm during the same query workload.",
    "Methods were allowed at most 48 hours to build a single index.",
    "During timed experiments, the server was used exclusively to ensure accurate measurements.",
    "For each query workload, we ran the experiment six times; we excluded the two best and worst, and reported the mean of the remaining performances.",
